THE Economic and Financial Crime Commission (EFCC) have arrested 18 suspected Internet fraudsters in Abuja. According to a statement released by the Commission, the suspects were arrested on July 4, 2022, at Trademore Estate, Lugbe, Abuja, following intelligence reports about their alleged involvement in Internet-related fraud. READ ALSO: Alleged N762.6m fraud: EFCC presents more witnesses against Nadabo Energy boss Rent your house to Yahoo boys, risk 15 years in jail, EFCC warns landlords Suspended Accountant-General released from EFCC custody Court remands Okorocha in EFCC custody over alleged N2.9bn fraud Ekiti: EFCC arrests persons involved in vote buying The suspects are: ThankGod Oche, Joshua Olohja, Adamu Abdulkadir, Â  David Bruno Bidemi, Emmanuel Avoh, Micheal Oche, Francis Abbah, Kayode Itodo, Shedrack Chibuike and Okeowo Elijah. Others are: Victor Emmanuel, Emmanuel Edache, Abah Joseph Theophilus, Sunday Agidani, Elijah Adamu, Emmanuel Ahme, Moses Agada and Adacole Michel. Items recovered from the suspects include a Lexus car, laptop computers, and mobile phones.